[src:probabilistic-programming/bayesian-network] Let *P* be a trail from node *u* to *v*.
[src:probabilistic-programming/bayesian-network] A trail is a loop-free, undirected (i.e. all edge directions are ignored) path between two nodes.
[src:probabilistic-programming/bayesian-network] The nodes *u* and *v* are *d*-separated by *Z* if all trails between them are *d*-separated.
